      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust FD3S Mazda RX-7, powered by the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This unit exhibits excellent compression and a seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbos at 4,500 RPM. The power is delivered through a precise 5-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque distribution during high-lateral-G cornering. The chassis utilizes its original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension geometry, offering the telepathic handling these cars are known for. Recent service includes a comprehensive vacuum line 'rat's nest' simplification and an upgraded aluminum multi-core radiator to enhance thermal management. While the finish shows light road wear, the structural integrity and drivetrain performance remain uncompromised, making this a premier candidate for a dedicated enthusiast.",
